For Students Gives General Practical Knowledge in Ethiopathogenesis, Diagnosis, Treatment and Prevention of Endocrine Diseases.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To Give Medical Students the Aim Knowledge of Endocrinology.
Teach them the Ethiopatogenesis, Symptoms, Diagnosis and  Treatment of Endocrine Diseases.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students that have passed this course: - have acquired knowledge of the  epidemiology, etiology, pathogenesis and clinical symptoms of the most common endocrine diseases - are aware of and can interpret the instrumental and laboratory research methods used in diagnosing and monitoring endocrine diseases; know the principles of treating and monitoring the most common endocrine diseases  - know how to interview and examine a patient with an endocrine disease (or suspected) - are able to independently interview and physically study a diabetic patient (assessment of diabetic neuropathy); can make research-based decisions regarding the alteration of the treatment of a diabetic patient; know how to examine and monitor a patient for complications caused by diabetes - are familiar with the different groups and know the major side effects of medication used in the treatment of diabetes - recognize a patient with endocrine disease that needs emergency care and can administer treatment in case of emergency (acute complications of diabetes, adrenal insufficiency)
